  "text": "As noticed in [39, p.99] , the number of dual-perfect points in P n modulo R >0 GL n (Z) is infinite in general. In [CITATION_1] , Bergé proved the following: Theorem 2.9 (Bergé) . The number of dual-extreme points in P n modulo R >0 GL n (Z) is finite. If a ∈ P n is dual extreme, then there exists λ ∈ R >0 such that λa ∈ GL n (Q). In particular , γ ",
